"title": "2411: cross, predictions of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2411",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The death of Jesus Christ fulfils OT predictions and was clearly anticipated in his teaching.</p>\n<h2>The cross foreshadowed in the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">GEN 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:6-Ps22:7\">PSA 22:6–22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:16-Ps22:18\">PSA 22:16–22:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:5\">PSA 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:21\">PSA 69:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:12-Isa52:13\">ISA 52:12–52:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:10\">ZEC 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:7</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ predicts his death on the cross</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's first announcement of his death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's second announcement of his death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:22-Matt17:23\">MAT 17:22–17:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:31\">MRK 9:31</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's third announcement of his death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:18–20:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:33–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:33\">LUK 18:31–18:33</a></p>\n<h2>Other allusions to the cross</h2>\n<h3>In the teaching of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:22\">MAT 20:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:38\">MRK 10:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:2\">MAT 26:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:19-Mark2:20\">MRK 2:19–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:44\">LUK 9:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>JHN <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:14\">3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:32-John12:33\">JHN 12:32–12:33</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:11\">JHN 18:11</a></p>\n<h3>In history</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:9-Matt17:13\">MAT 17:9–17:13</a></strong> <em>John the Baptist's fate indicates what is to happen to Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h3>In the experience of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:12\">MAT 26:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:8\">MRK 14:8</a> <em>Jesus Christ's reaction to the woman anointing him seems to suggest that he will die the death of a criminal.</em></p>\n<h3>In the Lord's Supper</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:25\">MRK 14:22–14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:19–22:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's perfect timing for Jesus Christ's death on the cross</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:4\">JHN 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:6\">JHN 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:8\">JHN 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:30\">JHN 7:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:20\">JHN 8:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1\">JHN 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></p>\n<h2>The curse of the cross</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:22-Deut21:23\">DEU 21:22–21:23</a></strong> <em>To be nailed to a cross is the equivalent of being hanged on a tree.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30\">ACT 5:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:10-Gal3:13\">GAL 3:10–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></p>",
